==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eviction
<hw>E*vic"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>evictio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧viction</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of evicting; or state of being
evicted; the recovery of lands, tenements, etc., from another's
possession by due course of law; dispossession by paramount title or
claim of such title; ejectment; ouster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conclusive evidence; proof.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Full <qex>eviction</qex> of this fatal truth.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Evidence</ent>⟦br⟧
